# Environment & Variable Strategy

## Objective
To understand how environment variables reduce hardcoded values and improve flexibility in API testing workflows.

---

## Environment Concept

In API testing, different environments often exist, such as:

- Development
- Staging
- Production

Each environment may have a different base URL.  
Using variables allows testers to switch environments without modifying every request manually.

Example base URLs:

```
http://dev.api.com
http://staging.api.com
http://api.com
```

Instead of hardcoding these URLs, a variable can be used.

---

## Base URL Variable

Example variable definition:

| Variable | Value |
|--------|--------|
| base_url | http://47.250.161.65:8080 |

API request can then be written as:

```
{{base_url}}/products
```

This improves maintainability because the base URL can be changed in a single location.

---

## Benefits of Using Variables

- Eliminates hardcoded URLs
- Simplifies environment switching
- Reduces manual updates across multiple requests
- Improves consistency in API testing workflows

---

## Example Usage

Instead of writing:

```
http://47.250.161.65:8080/products
```

Use:

```
{{base_url}}/products
```

If the API server changes, only the variable value needs to be updated.

---

## Dynamic Variables from Response

Variables can also be populated dynamically using response data.

Example response:

```json
{
  "id": 45,
  "name": "Ais"
}
```

Postman test script example:

```javascript
let jsonData = pm.response.json();
pm.environment.set("user_id", jsonData.id);
```

This script extracts the `id` value from the response and stores it as an environment variable.

---

## Example Request Chaining

After storing the variable:

```
{{user_id}} = 45
```

Subsequent requests can use it:

```
GET {{base_url}}/users/{{user_id}}
```

This enables request chaining and more realistic API testing flows.

---

## QA Relevance

Environment and variable strategies are essential for:

- Testing APIs across multiple environments
- Avoiding hardcoded configuration
- Supporting automated test workflows
- Enabling request chaining during functional testing
